   <conbody>
      <note type="warning" class="- topic/note ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Pressure air can cause personal injury.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">When using pressure air for cleaning, wear a protective face shield, protective clothing
        and protective shoes.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The maximum air pressure must be below 205 kPa (30 psi) for cleaning purposes.</p>
      </note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Compressed air, high pressure water or steam can be used to
remove dust, leaves and general debris from a radiator. Clean as
required by condition of radiator.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The use of compressed air is preferred.</p>
